    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that seems like a very straightforward explanation. if the data shows that people are choosing benefits over work because the math just doesn't add up for them, isn't it basically a settled fact that the current policy is driving the decline in participation? it feels like we're just describing a real-world effect at this point.",
