      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the economic model suggests a direct link, the real-world data is often muddied by other factors, which is why the debate persists. The decline in participation is also heavily influenced by structural issues like automation and the rise of precarious, low-wage gig work. Therefore, while policy choices certainly play a role, attributing the entire trend solely to the social safety net ignores massive shifts in the modern labor market.",
      "source": "target",
